.TH "PERFORMANCEMEASURE" "3JS" "November 6, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
PerformanceMeasure \- PerformanceMeasure
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
\f[B]\f[CB]PerformanceMeasure\f[B]\f[R] is an \f[I]abstract\f[R]
interface for \f[CR]PerformanceEntry\f[R] objects with an
\f[CR]entryType\f[R] of \f[CR]\(dqmeasure\(dq\f[R].
Entries of this type are created by calling
\f[CR]performance.measure()\f[R] to add a \f[I]named\f[R]
\f[CR]DOMHighResTimeStamp\f[R] (the \f[I]measure\f[R]) between two
\f[I]marks\f[R] to the browser\(cqs \f[I]performance timeline\f[R].
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
.TP
\f[B]PerformanceMeasure.detail\f[R]
Contains arbitrary metadata about the measure.
.PP
This interface extends the following \f[CR]PerformanceEntry\f[R]
properties by qualifying/constraining the properties as follows:
.TP
\f[B]PerformanceEntry.entryType\f[R]
Returns \f[CR]\(dqmeasure\(dq\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]PerformanceEntry.name\f[R]
Returns the name given to the measure when it was created via a call to
\f[CR]performance.measure()\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]PerformanceEntry.startTime\f[R]
Returns a \f[CR]timestamp\f[R] given to the measure when
\f[CR]performance.measure()\f[R] was called.
.TP
\f[B]PerformanceEntry.duration\f[R]
Returns a \f[CR]DOMHighResTimeStamp\f[R] that is the duration of the
measure (typically, the measure\(cqs end mark timestamp minus its start
mark timestamp).
.SH INSTANCE METHODS
This interface has no methods.
.SH EXAMPLE
See the example in Using the User Timing API.
.PP
Chrome DevTools uses \f[CR]performance.measure()\f[R] and in particular
a structured \f[CR]detail\f[R] property as part of its extensibility API
that surfaces these in custom tracks in performance traces.
See the example in Performance: measure() method page and the \c
.UR https://developer.chrome.com/docs/devtools/performance/extension#inject_your_data_with_the_user_timings_api
Chrome\(cqs extensibility API documentation
.UE \c
\ for more information and examples.
